Review_body:
Story-line => 4/5 (The plot is complex and unique. But the backstory is not explained clearly. Many questions remain unanswered. I liked the way the story writer predicted the 2020 Olympics in Japan. The story seems more relatable for today's modern society which is rotten to the bone.);
Acting => 5/5 (Syncing up with non-CGI animations seems like a lot of work. They pulled that off nicely.);
Directing => 5/5 (The movie is interesting from the beginning to the end. The presentation is nice. Loved the way it was directed.);
Animation => 5/5 (I was already amazed by this level of animation in 1988. Then I searched and found that no CGI was used to build up the whole thing. If that's not amazing, then I don't know what is.);
Screenplay => 4/5 (Due to unclear backstory and buildup, the dialogues were hard to understand and sometimes a bit bland. Overall, it's all right.);
Personal Recommendation => 5/5 (I would recommend everyone to watch this piece of artwork. You might find it complex. But a bit of background study will lead you to love this one.);
Most Favorite Character => Kaneda (Independent, Brave, Compassionate);Overall Personal Rating => 9.3/10
